:0 0 6px;color:#f8fafc;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;\">&#10060; SRRK &mdash; Scholar Rock Holding &nbsp;<span style=\"background:#2a1515;color:#f87171;font-size:10px;font-weight:600;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;\">SKIP</span></p><p style=\"margin:0;color:#94a3b8;font-size:12px;\">Market cap ~$6.3B (Gate 2 fail: &gt;$2B). Event &gt;45 days out (Gate 1 fail). Eliminated on two gates.</p></td></tr></table><table width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#0f1f2e;border-radius:6px;\"><tr><td style=\"padding:14px 16px;\"><p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;color:#f8fafc;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;\">&#10060; IMNM &mdash; Immunome &nbsp;<span style=\"background:#2a1515;color:#f87171;font-size:10px;font-weight:600;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;\">SKIP</span></p><p style=\"margin:0;color:#94a3b8;font-size:12px;\">No confirmed PDUFA date found (Gate 1 fail). Cannot establish binary event window. Monitor for date confirmation.</p></td></tr></table><p style=\"margin:12px 0 0;color:#64748b;font-size:11px;\">Honest finding: No new catalyst plays qualify beyond CAPR, which is already being tracked. Zero new entries today &mdash; all $352.56 cash stays as dry powder.</p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"background:#0f172a;padding:16px 28px 8px;\"><p style=\"margin:0;color:#475569;font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1.5px;font-weight:600;\">&#9656; Watchlist</p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"background:#1e293b;padding:16px 28px;border-top:1px solid #334155;\"><table width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\"><tr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #334155;\"><td style=\"padding:10px 8px 10px 0;color:#f8fafc;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;width:18%;\">CAPR</td><td style=\"padding:10px 4px;color:#94a3b8;font-size:12px;width:28%;\">$23.22 <span style=\"color:#10b981;font-size:11px;\">(below $26 target &#10003;)</span></td><td style=\"padding:10px 4px;color:#fbbf24;font-size:11px;width:26%;\">&#128993; SOON &mdash; AdCom Jul 29</td><td style=\"padding:10px 0 10px 4px;font-size:11px;width:28%;\"><span style=\"background:#1c3a1c;color:#4ade80;font-size:10px;font-weight:600;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;\">WATCH</span> &middot; Enter post-July 7</td></tr><tr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #334155;\"><td style=\"padding:10px 8px 10px 0;color:#64748b;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;\">VRDN</td><td style=\"padding:10px 4px;color:#64748b;font-size:12px;\">Approved Jun 30</td><td style=\"padding:10px 4px;color:#64748b;font-size:11px;\">Entry missed (IBKR)</td><td style=\"padding:10px 0 10px 4px;\"><span style=\"background:#1e293b;color:#64748b;font-size:10px;font-weight:600;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;border:1px solid #334155;\">ARCHIVED</span></td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:10px 8px 10px 0;color:#64748b;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;\">VERA (WL)</td><td style=\"padding:10px 4px;color:#64748b;font-size:12px;\">Active position</td><td style=\"padding:10px 4px;color:#64748b;font-size:11px;\">See Holdings</td><td style=\"padding:10px 0 10px 4px;\"><span style=\"background:#1e293b;color:#64748b;font-size:10px;font-weight:600;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;border:1px solid #334155;\">ARCHIVED</span></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td style=\"background:#0f172a;padding:16px 28px 8px;\"><p style=\"margin:0;color:#475569;font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1.5px;font-weight:600;\">&#9656; Cash Deployment Plan</p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"background:#1e293b;padding:16px 28px;border-top:1px solid #334155;\"><p style=\"margin:0 0 8px;color:#f8fafc;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;\">&#128176; Available: $352.56 &nbsp;|&nbsp; Status: <span style=\"color:#fbbf24;\">HOLD &mdash; DRY POWDER</span></p><p style=\"margin:0 0 12px;color:#94a3b8;font-size:12px;\">You are 23 hours from the most consequential binary event in this portfolio&apos;s history. No new positions until July 7 result is known.</p><table width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\"><tr><td style=\"width:49%;padding-right:10px;vertical-align:top;\"><p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;color:#10b981;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;\">&#10003; If VERA approved July 7:</p><p style=\"margin:0;color:#94a3b8;font-size:12px;\">Enter CAPR ~$23 (better than $26 original target). Size ~$150. Hold remaining ~$200 for further rotation. VERA TP1 proceeds ($55) deploy into analyst-level targets.</p></td><td style=\"width:49%;padding-left:10px;vertical-align:top;border-left:1px solid #334155;\"><p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;color:#ef4444;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;\">&#128128; If VERA CRL July 7:</p><p style=\"margin:0;color:#94a3b8;font-size:12px;\">VERA gaps to $10&ndash;15. Stop at $24.50 will not catch the gap. Net loss ~$150&ndash;165. Cash $352.56 becomes survival capital. ANET stop ($144) stays. Reassess full portfolio before any new entry.</p></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td style=\"background:#0f172a;padding:16px 28px 8px;\"><p style=\"margin:0;color:#475569;font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1.5px;font-weight:600;\">&#9656; Education &mdash; Concept #14</p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"background:#1e293b;padding:20px 28px;border-top:1px solid #334155;border-left:3px solid #8b5cf6;\"><p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#a78bfa;font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;\">Today&apos;s Concept</p><p style=\"margin:0 0 14px;color:#f8fafc;font-size:16px;font-weight:700;\">TAM &mdash; Total Addressable Market</p><p style=\"margin:0 0 10px;color:#cbd5e1;font-size:13px;line-height:1.6;\"><strong style=\"color:#f8fafc;\">What it is:</strong> TAM is the total annual revenue a product could capture if it held 100% of its target market. It sets the ceiling for how big a company can get. In biotech, TAM tells you whether the analyst price target is plausible &mdash; or already baked in.</p><p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;color:#f8fafc;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;\">VERA&apos;s case &mdash; IgAN market:</p><table width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#0f172a;border-radius:6px;margin-bottom:12px;\"><tr><td style=\"padding:12px 14px;\"><p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;color:#94a3b8;font-size:12px;\">&#8226; IgAN global market: <strong style=\"color:#f8fafc;\">$730M in 2024</strong>, growing at 30.5% CAGR</p><p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;color:#94a3b8;font-size:12px;\">&#8226; Projected to reach <strong style=\"color:#f8fafc;\">~$3B+ by 2030</strong> as IgAN awareness and diagnosis rates improve</p><p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;color:#94a3b8;font-size:12px;\">&#8226; Atacicept peak sales potential: <strong style=\"color:#f8fafc;\">$450M&ndash;$750M</strong> (20&ndash;30% market share if approved)</p><p style=\"margin:0;color:#94a3b8;font-size:12px;\">&#8226; At $750M peak sales &times; 5&times; biotech revenue multiple &rarr; <strong style=\"color:#f8fafc;\">$3.75B market cap</strong> &asymp; stock price $80&ndash;100</p></td></tr></table><p style=\"margin:0 0 10px;color:#cbd5e1;font-size:13px;line-height:1.6;\"><strong style=\"color:#f8fafc;\">Related: &ldquo;Peak sales&rdquo;</strong> = the maximum annual revenue a drug is expected to generate, typically 5&ndash;8 years after launch. Analysts model this number and work backwards to set price targets. That&apos;s why VERA&apos;s 14-analyst consensus of $68&ndash;83 isn&apos;t arbitrary &mdash; it&apos;s anchored to $450M&ndash;$750M peak sales divided by shares outstanding.</p><p style=\"margin:0 0 10px;color:#cbd5e1;font-size:13px;line-height:1.6;\"><strong style=\"color:#f8fafc;\">Why it matters for you:</strong> In FX you size positions relative to pip value and account equity. In biotech you size relative to TAM &times; market share probability. Same discipline, different frame. When a biotech&apos;s market cap already prices in 50% TAM penetration and Phase 2 data, the risk/reward collapses &mdash; the stock has nowhere to go on approval.</p><p style=\"margin:0;color:#7c3aed;font-size:11px;border-top:1px solid #334155;padding-top:10px;\">&#128218; Concept 14 of 30 &middot; Next: Earnings revision cycles &mdash; how analysts move targets post-catalyst</p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"background:#0f172a;padding:16px 28px 8px;\"><p style=\"margin:0;color:#475569;font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1.5px;font-weight:600;\">&#9656; Upcoming Schedule</p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"background:#1e293b;padding:16px 28px;border-top:1px solid #334155;\"><p style=\"margin:0 0 8px;color:#fca5a5;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;\">&#128680; TOMORROW July 3 &mdash; NYSE CLOSED. No daily email.</p><p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;color:#94a3b8;font-size:12px;\">&#8226; <strong style=\"color:#f8fafc;\">Saturday&ndash;Sunday July 5&ndash;6:</strong> No email (weekend, no market)</p><p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;color:#94a3b8;font-size:12px;\">&#8226; <strong style=\"color:#f8fafc;\">Monday July 7 AM:</strong> Pre-PDUFA note + ANET check</p><p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;color:#fbbf24;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;\">&#8226; &#128680; TUESDAY JULY 7: VERA PDUFA. FDA can act any time this day. Keep phone close. Check IBKR app every few hours.</p><p style=\"margin:0;color:#94a3b8;font-size:12px;\">&#8226; <strong style=\"color:#f8fafc;\">July 29:</strong> CAPR AdCom (enter ~$23 if VERA approved)</p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"background:#0f172a;padding:16px 28px;border-top:1px solid #1e293b;\"><p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#475569;font-size:11px;\">&#128197; Report: Thursday, July 2, 2026 &middot; Kuwait time (AST UTC+3)</p><p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#475569;font-size:11px;\">&#128176; Prices: Web-sourced June 30 close &mdash; IBKR connector offline this run</p><p style=\"margin:0;color:#3b4a5a;font-size:10px;margin-top:8px;\">Automated research, not financial advice. Halal compliance per AAOIFI standards. Verify via Musaffa before new entries.</p></td></tr></table></td></tr></table></body></html>"
